<LegalLayout
  locale="en"
  eyebrow="Cookies"
  title="Cookie policy"
  description="Scluba cookie policy — types of cookies, purposes, retention, and how to manage your preferences."
  altPathname="/legal/cookies/"
  updated="2026-05-06"
>
  <h2>1. What is a cookie?</h2>
  <p>
    A cookie is a small file placed on your device (computer, smartphone, tablet) when you visit a
    website or web application. It can be used to remember preferences, authenticate a session,
    or measure site audience.
  </p>
  <p>
    This policy describes the types of cookies used by <a href="https://scluba.com">scluba.com</a>
    and the Scluba app (hereinafter the <strong>"Site"</strong>), their purposes, their retention,
    and how to exercise your choices.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Our philosophy: minimalist</h2>
  <p>
    Scluba has chosen a <strong>minimalist use of cookies</strong>. To date, we use no advertising
    cookies, no profiling cookies, and no social-network pixels. We only set
    <strong>strictly necessary</strong> cookies for the Site to function and, where applicable,
    audience-measurement cookies exempt from consent (privacy-first configuration).
  </p>

  <h2>3. Cookies in use</h2>

  <h3>3.1 Strictly necessary cookies</h3>
  <p>
    These cookies are essential for the Site to function and cannot be disabled from our systems.
    They store no identification data allowing you to be recognized for commercial purposes.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Cookie</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Retention</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>sb-*</code> (Supabase)</td>
        <td>Maintain the authentication session (ops area, player accounts)</td>
        <td>Session or until logout</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>scluba-locale</code></td>
        <td>Remember chosen language (FR / EN)</td>
        <td>12 months</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>scluba-consent</code></td>
        <td>Remember your choice regarding optional cookies</td>
        <td>13 months</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    In accordance with French data protection authority (CNIL) guidance, these cookies are
    <strong>exempt from consent</strong> as they are strictly necessary for the provision of the
    service expressly requested.
  </p>

  <h3>3.2 Audience measurement (consent-exempt)</h3>
  <p>
    If we use an analytics tool, we configure it in privacy-first mode
    (No third-party analytics during pilot phase):
    no identification cookie, anonymized IP, data hosted in the EU, no cross-referencing with other
    processing. This scope falls under the consent exemption defined by the CNIL.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Tool</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Retention</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>None</td>
        <td>Anonymous visit statistics (page views, aggregated traffic source)</td>
        <td>No persistent cookie or 24h-max cookie</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>3.3 Third-party cookies</h3>
  <p>
    We do not embed any advertising pixel (Google Ads, Meta Pixel, TikTok, LinkedIn Insight Tag,
    etc.) on the Site.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use the recap card's social-share feature (Instagram, WhatsApp, X, Facebook…), your
    phone's native app takes over. No cookie is set by Scluba on this occasion. The destination
    platforms' terms then apply.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Your choices</h2>
  <p>
    You can at any time:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>configure your browser</strong> to block or delete cookies (under "preferences" or "privacy" in your browser);</li>
    <li>use <strong>private browsing</strong> mode;</li>
    <li>write to <a href="mailto:team@scluba.com">team@scluba.com</a> with any question.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Blocking strictly necessary cookies may prevent some Site features from working properly (in
    particular login to secured areas).
  </p>

  <h3>4.1 Useful links to browser settings</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Chrome</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enhanced-tracking-protection-firefox-desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Safari</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Updates</h2>
  <p>
    This cookie policy may be updated. The applicable version is the one displayed at the top of
    the page. Any substantial change is brought to your attention by appropriate means.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For any question: <a href="mailto:team@scluba.com">team@scluba.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
